Dangote Cement Plc, the biggest company on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) by market capitalization, recorded its biggest gain in over four years. The stock rose by 9.73 percent to close at N203 on Wednesday, the biggest gain recorded by the cement giant at the domestic bourse since April 1, 2015 Since the listing of MTN Nigeria on the NSE on Thursday, many investors have been unable to purchase the shares of the telecoms company. 